docs {
  Ingest the extended team dataset (22 messages) for the graph demo.

  The dataset is designed to demonstrate graph-enhanced retrieval:

  - 10 messages about Project Atlas (people, technologies, dependencies)
  - 3 messages about Bob (TensorFlow expert, NO mention of Atlas)
  - 9 noise messages (other projects, company, people)

  KEY INSIGHT: Bob never mentions "Project Atlas" or "dependencies"
  in any of his messages.  His only connection to Atlas is through
  TensorFlow â€” which Atlas uses as an ML dependency.  With a pure
  vector search (top_k=5), Bob's messages rank low because they
  don't share vocabulary with Atlas queries.  With graph-enhanced
  retrieval, the system discovers Bob through the shared TensorFlow
  connection in the knowledge graph.

  Run "00 Delete Project" first for a clean slate.  After ingestion,
  wait ~10 seconds for semantic feature extraction to complete before
  running searches.
}
